summary: The President's Intelligence Checklist from November 25, 1963, covers various global hotspots including South Vietnam, Indonesia-Malaysia, Venezuela, Iraq, Syria, Italy, and UAR-Yemen-Egypt, along with notes on Oswald's visit to embassies in Mexico City, military promotions in Brazil, Soviet ship activity near Johnston Island, potential coup in Algeria, Australian grain contracts with China, Soviet embassy activity in Congo, Berlin access routes, and neutralist gains in Laos.
title: THE PRESIDENT'S INTELLIGENCE CHECKLIST
